<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The call strlen(realm) has no prior validation of the pointer. If realm is NULL this call dereferences a null pointer; if realm does not point to a NUL-terminated object, strlen will read past the object bounds. Either case results in out-of-bounds access of the object referenced by the pointer parameter and thus violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 21.17.
</scenario>

